âJohansen!â Wolf Larsen called out.  A sailor stepped forward obediently.
âGet your palm and needle and sew the beggar up.  Youâll find some old
canvas in the sail-locker.  Make it do.â

âWhatâll I put on his feet, sir?â the man asked, after the customary âAy,
ay, sir.â

âWeâll see to that,â Wolf Larsen answered, and elevated his voice in a
