âBut there is,â I objected.  âIt is still obscure to me.â

âWhat can I tell you?â he demanded, with a recrudescence of fierceness.
âOf the meagreness of a childâs life? of fish diet and coarse living? of
going out with the boats from the time I could crawl? of my brothers, who
went away one by one to the deep-sea farming and never came back? of
