âYonson,â he began.

âMy name is Johnson, sir,â the sailor boldly corrected.

âWell, Johnson, then, damn you!  Can you guess why I have sent for you?â

âYes, and no, sir,â was the slow reply.  âMy work is done well.  The mate
knows that, and you know it, sir.  So there cannot be any complaint.â

âAnd is that all?â Wolf Larsen queried, his voice soft, and low, and
