pulse rushed up in an unwonted manner, yet my rage mounted with it.  She
looked me bravely in the eyes.

âFor my sake,â she begged.

âI would kill him for your sake!â I cried, trying to free my arm without
hurting her.

âHush!â she said, and laid her fingers lightly on my lips.  I could have
kissed them, had I dared, even then, in my rage, the touch of them was so
