âVan Weyden!â he called hoarsely, and with a note of fright in his
voice.  âOh, Van Weyden! where are you?â

I looked at Maud.  She did not speak, but nodded her head.

âHere I am,â I answered, stepping to his side.  âWhat is the matter?â

âHelp me to a seat,â he said, in the same hoarse, frightened voice.

âI am a sick man; a very sick man, Hump,â he said, as he left my
sustaining grip and sank into a chair.

His head dropped forward on the table and was buried in his hands.  From
