frightened.  What had happened to him we could not imagine.

âHump,â he said at last, âI must get into my bunk.  Lend me a hand.  Iâll
be all right in a little while.  Itâs those damn headaches, I believe.  I
was afraid of them.  I had a feelingâno, I donât know what Iâm talking
about.  Help me into my bunk.â

But when I got him into his bunk he again buried his face in his hands,
