She shook her head.  âI saw nothing.  It is just as mysterious to me.  He
suddenly released me and staggered away.  But what shall we do?  What
shall I do?â

âIf you will wait, please, until I come back,â I answered.

I went on deck.  Louis was at the wheel.

âYou may go forâard and turn in,â I said, taking it from him.

He was quick to obey, and I found myself alone on the deck of the
