âWill you trust yourself to me for a journey of six hundred miles or so?â
I asked.

âYou meanâ?â she asked, and I knew she had guessed aright.

âYes, I mean just that,â I replied.  âThere is nothing left for us but
the open boat.â

âFor me, you mean,â she said.  âYou are certainly as safe here as you
have been.â

âNo, there is nothing left for us but the open boat,â I iterated stoutly.
âWill you please dress as warmly as you can, at once, and make into a
