âYou might have suggested a window when the walls were going up,â I said.
âIt was for you, and you should have seen the need of a window.â

âBut I never do see the obvious, you know,â she laughed back.  âAnd
besides, you can knock a hole in the wall at any time.â

âQuite true; I had not thought of it,â I replied, wagging my head sagely.
âBut have you thought of ordering the window-glass?  Just call up the
