âOh, you brave, brave woman,â I said, when I saw the life coming back
into her face.  âDid you know that you were brave?â

âI never used to be,â she answered.  âI was never brave till I knew you.
It is you who have made me brave.â

âNor I, until I knew you,â I answered.

She gave me a quick look, and again I caught that dancing, tremulous
