a sea voyage, and I chose the longest.â

âYou little knew what you were choosing,â I laughed.

âBut I shall be a different women for the experience, as well as a
stronger woman,â she answered; âand, I hope a better woman.  At least I
shall understand a great deal more of life.â

Then, as the short day waned, we fell to discussing Wolf Larsenâs
blindness.  It was inexplicable.  And that it was grave, I instanced his
